  "instructions": [
    "Bring a large pot of water to boil over high. Prepare the lotus root: Using a sharp peeler, peel the lotus root, wash it, then thinly slice it crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick rounds.",
    "Once the water boils, cook the lotus root in the boiling water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer lotus root to a large bowl.",
    "Add the edamame to the boiling water; cook about 1 minute then transfer to another bowl.",
    "Heat the oil in a large wok or nonstick skillet over medium-high. Once the oil is hot, add the lotus root and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Add about Â½ cup water to prevent the slices from browning, then add the edamame and peppers; season with the mushroom seasoning (if using), sugar and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until the peppers are softened, about 2 minutes. Season to taste with salt and serve with rice."
